Preheat your #oven to 220°C. Peel the @garlic cloves{1}, and pop into #foil with a drizzle of @oil{} and scrunch to enclose it. Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Pop the garlic and pepper on a #baking tray{}, drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast in your oven until soft, ~{10-12%mins}.

Zest and halve the @lemon{1/2}. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}. Pop the @diced chicken breast{260%g} into a #bowl with the lemon zest, half the @low fat natural yoghurt{75%g}, the @harissa paste{50%g}, a drizzle of @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Mix well and set aside.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling chicken and its packaging.

Trim the root from the @baby gem lettuce{1} then separate the leaves. Trim and finely slice the @radishes{100%g}. Pop the lettuce and radishes into a #bowl and set aside.

Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the chicken with its marinade and cook, stirring frequently, until golden brown, ~{4-5%mins}. Add the red onion to the chicken pan and cook until the onion is soft and the chicken is cooked through, ~{4-5%mins}. Once the garlic is roasted, transfer to a #board and mash with the back of a #fork until smooth. Stir the pepper into the chicken mixture.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Pop the remaining yoghurt into a #small bowl{} with the mashed roasted garlic, half the lemon juice and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Mix together and set aside. Pop the @garlic and coriander naans{4} onto a baking tray and put in the oven until warmed through, ~{2-3%mins}. Add the remaining lemon juice and @olive oil{1} to the salad. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and mix together.

Divide the warmed naans between your plates. Top with the chicken and drizzle over the roasted garlic yoghurt. Serve with the salad alongside. Enjoy!

> If you've opted to get chicken breast instead of thigh, cook the chicken breast in the same way the recipe tells you to cook the chicken thigh.